 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "MetalFabAdvisor ⊣ Metal Fabrication Plant Operations Governor,
 langgraph-clj StateGraph, append-only audit ledger. A plant
 OPERATIONS COORDINATION actor for a metal-fabrication shop
 (stamping-press -> pressing-line -> wire-forming production line)
 producing miscellaneous n.e.c. fabricated metal products (stamped/
 pressed sheet-metal parts, wire products, metal household goods) --
 not direct stamping/pressing-line-equipment control authority. Four
 ops (`:log-production-batch` / `:schedule-maintenance` /
 `:flag-safety-concern` / `:coordinate-shipment`), all `:effect
 :propose` only. Ten concrete governor checks elaborate this
 blueprint's four HARD invariants: propose-only effect, closed op
 allowlist, closed proposal-effect allowlist (no direct stamping/
 pressing-line-equipment control), permanent press-line-actuate block,
 independent equipment verification/registration before maintenance
 scheduling, independent batch verification/registration before
 shipment coordination, independent shipment-weight recompute against
 the batch's own logged weight, double-schedule guard, product-
 category validation, and defect-rate plausibility validation.
 Safety-concern flagging (sharp-edge/burr-laceration/press-pinch-point/
 wire-entanglement/coating-chemical-exposure) ALWAYS escalates to a
 human shop supervisor; `:log-production-batch` is the only op
 eligible to auto-commit, and only at phase 3 when governor-clean."}
